114
00:12:59,660 --> 00:13:02,180
Okay. One moment, Hye Ri.

115
00:13:10,660 --> 00:13:13,970
 Is something the matter, Hye Ri? 

116
00:13:15,850 --> 00:13:17,850
Doctor,

117
00:13:17,850 --> 00:13:21,500
I'm Eun Ho. Ju Eun Ho.

118
00:13:23,180 --> 00:13:28,830
Doctor, have I been coming here saying that I'm Hye Ri?

119
00:13:31,290 --> 00:13:32,750
Yes.

120
00:13:32,750 --> 00:13:35,040
- The thing is... 
 - Since when?

121
00:13:35,040 --> 00:13:37,210
Since when have I been doing that?

122
00:13:37,210 --> 00:13:41,260
What state was I in? Was I not like how I am now?

123
00:13:42,250 --> 00:13:44,440
Doctor, I don't recall any of it.

124
00:13:44,440 --> 00:13:47,210
I keep falling asleep in strange places.

125
00:13:47,210 --> 00:13:50,510
I meet strangers. My phone suddenly disappeared.

126
00:13:50,510 --> 00:13:52,630
And sometimes...

127
00:13:54,020 --> 00:13:56,150
Occasionally...

128
00:13:57,220 --> 00:14:00,300
I remember things I don't recognize.

129
00:14:00,300 --> 00:14:05,330
I don't know what they are, and I don't seem myself inside those memories.

130
00:14:05,330 --> 00:14:08,550
I read a letter I wrote to myself when I was living as Hye Ri.

131
00:14:08,550 --> 00:14:10,880
It wasn't a letter I would write.

132
00:14:10,880 --> 00:14:15,500
I can't believe it. I don't recall writing that letter.

133
00:14:15,500 --> 00:14:17,060
Really...

134
00:14:17,060 --> 00:14:20,900
I can't ponder it because I hate thinking of it.

135
00:14:21,990 --> 00:14:24,170
Eun Ho,

136
00:14:24,170 --> 00:14:26,800
it must have been so confusing for you.

137
00:14:26,800 --> 00:14:28,830
That's natural.

138
00:14:28,830 --> 00:14:32,350
Then could you tell me...

139
00:14:32,350 --> 00:14:35,900
what Hye Ri is like? The one who wrote you a letter.

140
00:14:35,900 --> 00:14:40,300
If you could tell me what kind of person she is...

141
00:14:55,440 --> 00:14:57,330
Hye Ri is...

142
00:15:03,020 --> 00:15:05,860
I mean, Hye Ri...

143
00:15:05,860 --> 00:15:07,410
Yes.

144
00:15:13,580 --> 00:15:15,830
is my younger sister...

145
00:15:21,950 --> 00:15:24,320
who went missing.

146
00:15:30,500 --> 00:15:33,100
 Hye Ri, listen carefully. 

147
00:15:33,100 --> 00:15:37,900
 From now on, we can't see Mom and Dad again. 

148
00:15:38,850 --> 00:15:42,570
 - Why not? Because of the accident? 
 - Yes. 

149
00:15:42,570 --> 00:15:45,270
 It was a big accident. 

150
00:15:45,270 --> 00:15:46,580
 So... 

151
00:15:46,580 --> 00:15:48,970
 Oppa, you have the most money! 

152
00:15:48,970 --> 00:15:50,760
 You should take them! 

153
00:15:50,760 --> 00:15:53,240
 Why are you bringing that up right now? 

154
00:15:53,240 --> 00:15:55,360
 We don't even have a house. 

155
00:15:55,360 --> 00:15:57,390
 Our place is collateral right now. 

156
00:15:57,390 --> 00:16:00,060
 We're about to be homeless. 

157
00:16:00,060 --> 00:16:03,460
 We can't take care of them! 

158
00:16:03,460 --> 00:16:06,450
 You used to borrow money so often. Now you're scared to take them? 

159
00:16:06,450 --> 00:16:09,090
 I'm busy trying to put food in my mouth. 

160
00:16:09,090 --> 00:16:13,050
 How are we supposed to take care of them? 

161
00:16:13,050 --> 00:16:16,020
 You take care of them. You have the most money! 

162
00:16:16,020 --> 00:16:19,400
 Frankly, you took all of our dad's assets. 

163
00:16:19,400 --> 00:16:25,000
 - We live like beggars while you flaunt your wealth. 
 - Hey! 

164
00:16:25,000 --> 00:16:26,570
 Are you serious right now? 

165
00:16:26,570 --> 00:16:28,950
 Oppa, you never did anything for Dad. 

166
00:16:28,950 --> 00:16:31,410
 During Dad's later years, you looked the other way! 

167
00:16:31,410 --> 00:16:33,780
 - It's okay, Hye Ri. 
 - And you had the nerve 

168
00:16:33,780 --> 00:16:37,240
 - You have me. 
 - to take all of his assets? 

169
00:16:37,240 --> 00:16:39,650
 All you need to do is send them to an orphanage. 

170
00:16:39,650 --> 00:16:42,000
 - That's dirty. 
 - Why talk to me so rudely due to them? 

171
00:16:42,880 --> 00:16:45,200
 - Don't do that. It's dirty. 
 - Just send them to an orphanage! 

172
00:16:45,200 --> 00:16:49,900
 You don't have parents anymore. You need to care for yourselves. 

173
00:16:51,220 --> 00:16:52,870
 Here. 

174
00:16:54,200 --> 00:16:55,810
 Hey. 

175
00:16:57,530 --> 00:16:59,870
 Blow your nose. Blow. 

176
00:16:59,870 --> 00:17:01,830
 Good. One more time. 

177
00:17:01,830 --> 00:17:04,060
 Good. 

178
00:17:06,050 --> 00:17:08,450
 Who are you? 

179
00:17:11,190 --> 00:17:13,070
 Grandma? 

180
00:17:13,670 --> 00:17:15,760
 That's right! 

181
00:17:16,380 --> 00:17:20,820
 You've always been smart. You remember me! 

182
00:17:20,820 --> 00:17:23,010
 You're Eun Ho, right? 

183
00:17:25,760 --> 00:17:27,470
 Then are you Hye Ri? 

184
00:17:27,470 --> 00:17:30,180
 Yes, I'm Hye Ri. 

185
00:17:30,950 --> 00:17:33,050
 Hye Ri, 

186
00:17:33,050 --> 00:17:35,780
 do you want to come with Grandma? 

187
00:17:35,780 --> 00:17:38,870
 Want to come live with Grandma? 

188
00:17:48,250 --> 00:17:51,670
 Unnie, you know what? I received an academic warning. 

189
00:17:51,670 --> 00:17:53,530
 Hey, you need to study. 

190
00:17:53,530 --> 00:17:56,310
 You can't do that while studying with a stranger's money. 

191
00:17:56,310 --> 00:17:58,400
 I'm sorry. 

192
00:17:58,400 --> 00:18:02,700
 But, Unnie, why is Grandma a stranger? 

193
00:18:02,700 --> 00:18:04,840
 She is. 

194
00:18:04,840 --> 00:18:07,100
 Do you know how distantly related we are in the family tree? 

195
00:18:07,100 --> 00:18:12,400
 She raised us anyway so we basically owe her. 

196
00:18:14,270 --> 00:18:16,800
 Plus, we will move out. I signed the lease on a place. 

197
00:18:16,800 --> 00:18:19,120
 You'll live downstairs, and I'll live upstairs. 

198
00:18:19,120 --> 00:18:22,200
 What are you talking about? Why would we leave? 

199
00:18:22,200 --> 00:18:25,500
 Hye Ri, if we don't leave, will you live here forever? 

200
00:18:25,500 --> 00:18:27,740
 Yes. Of course. 

201
00:18:27,740 --> 00:18:30,680
 Grandma will be bored without us. 

202
00:18:33,280 --> 00:18:35,570
 Listen to me, Ju Hye Ri. 

203
00:18:36,500 --> 00:18:40,600
 No one in this world is generous without wanting something in return. 

204
00:18:41,720 --> 00:18:44,720
 That's not true. Grandma is kind for nothing in return. 

205
00:18:44,720 --> 00:18:47,430
 And it's not because she's generous. 

206
00:18:47,430 --> 00:18:50,260
 She just loves us. 

207
00:18:52,880 --> 00:18:55,200
 "Love"? It's just debt. 

208
00:18:55,200 --> 00:18:58,350
 Unnie, you're so weird. 

209
00:18:58,350 --> 00:19:01,430
 I don't understand anything you're saying. 

210
00:19:18,800 --> 00:19:21,260
 A graduation trip? 

211
00:19:21,260 --> 00:19:25,100
 You have to go. You should definitely go. 

212
00:19:26,730 --> 00:19:28,880
 Go on the graduation trip. 

213
00:19:28,880 --> 00:19:31,160
 You have no friends because you don't go to things like that. 

214
00:19:31,160 --> 00:19:33,380
 I don't want to go. 

215
00:19:33,380 --> 00:19:35,340
 I really don't. 

216
00:19:35,340 --> 00:19:37,050
 Why don't you want to go? 

217
00:19:37,050 --> 00:19:38,860
 I like being home better. 

218
00:19:38,860 --> 00:19:41,460
 I don't have any friends there. 

219
00:19:43,010 --> 00:19:45,990
 You can make friends there. 

220
00:19:45,990 --> 00:19:49,500
 How can you have no friends even as you're graduating college? 

221
00:19:49,500 --> 00:19:50,950
 Go make some. 

222
00:19:50,950 --> 00:19:54,990
 That's how you can be helpful when you step into society. 

223
00:19:54,990 --> 00:19:57,700
 I told you that you need to be independent now. 

224
00:19:57,700 --> 00:20:01,200
 I found a place you can live in, Ju Hye Ri. 

225
00:20:01,200 --> 00:20:03,290
 But I really— 

226
00:20:03,290 --> 00:20:05,120
 Go. 

227
00:20:05,120 --> 00:20:07,750
 I'll assume you're going. 

228
00:20:07,750 --> 00:20:09,780
 I can send the money to this account, right? 

229
00:20:09,780 --> 00:20:13,210
 But I really don't want to go, Unnie. 

230
00:20:13,210 --> 00:20:15,780
 I don't need friends. 

231
00:20:15,780 --> 00:20:17,400
 I'm not going. 

232
00:20:17,400 --> 00:20:19,580
 All I need is you, Unnie. 

233
00:20:19,580 --> 00:20:21,270
 Ju Hye Ri! 

234
00:20:21,270 --> 00:20:23,240
 How long are you going to be like this? 

235
00:20:23,240 --> 00:20:25,330
 You need to be independent! 

236
00:20:25,330 --> 00:20:28,860
 Work hard at something! Make connections! 

237
00:20:28,860 --> 00:20:31,800
 You need to get ready to be a part of society! 

238
00:20:32,940 --> 00:20:34,730
 Stop complaining and go. 

239
00:20:34,730 --> 00:20:37,180
 Go make friends! 

240
00:20:49,290 --> 00:20:51,430
 Yes, hello? 

241
00:20:54,380 --> 00:20:56,680
 I'm sorry. 

242
00:20:57,390 --> 00:21:00,060
 Could you say that again? 

243
00:21:00,060 --> 00:21:02,460
 Ju Hye Ri is missing. 

244
00:21:03,080 --> 00:21:04,900
 Hey, Eun Ho. 

245
00:21:04,900 --> 00:21:10,230
 Hye Ri hasn't been answering her phone since yesterday. 

246
00:21:10,230 --> 00:21:12,360
 Did something happen? 

247
00:21:24,800 --> 00:21:27,280
 Hye... Hye Ri... 

248
00:21:27,280 --> 00:21:32,130
 "A", a college student who went on a graduation trip, was reported missing last night. 

249
00:21:49,950 --> 00:21:53,480
   

250
00:22:00,210 --> 00:22:02,600
 Grandma. 

251
00:22:05,400 --> 00:22:07,680
 Grandma, are you there? 

252
00:22:14,100 --> 00:22:17,600
 Grandma, you know... 

253
00:22:18,720 --> 00:22:23,200
 let's wait for Hye Ri a little longer, as you said. 

254
00:22:27,080 --> 00:22:28,810
 Grandma. 

255
00:22:37,230 --> 00:22:39,010
 Grandma? 

256
00:22:45,560 --> 00:22:47,510
 Grandma... 

257
00:22:52,770 --> 00:22:54,760
 Grandma! 

258
00:22:56,580 --> 00:22:58,950
 Grandma! 

259
00:22:59,920 --> 00:23:02,270
 Grandma! 

260
