00:24:00,960 --> 00:24:05,000
 - that'd be difficult. 
 - My sister really wanted to do this, 

270
00:24:06,630 --> 00:24:09,120
 though I don't know why. 

271
00:24:25,130 --> 00:24:27,120
 Sunbae, what is it? 

272
00:24:28,100 --> 00:24:30,250
 I want to do the morning radio. 

273
00:24:30,250 --> 00:24:34,590
 I know there's an opening. Plug (place) me there. 

274
00:24:34,590 --> 00:24:36,900
 I can't work at night. 

275
00:24:37,540 --> 00:24:38,750
 Hye Ri! 

276
00:24:38,750 --> 00:24:41,160
 I'm busy. Don't call me at this hour from now on. 

277
00:24:41,160 --> 00:24:43,400
 Don't ever ask why. 

278
00:24:47,270 --> 00:24:49,750
 - The administrative office. 
 - Yes. 

279
00:24:51,160 --> 00:24:53,790
 I wanted to live that life, 

280
00:24:53,790 --> 00:24:58,660
 doing the work she might have done here. 

281
00:24:58,660 --> 00:25:02,680
 If I lived like her, who was truly happy, 

282
00:25:02,680 --> 00:25:05,920
 could I be happy as well? 

283
00:25:05,920 --> 00:25:10,950
 So did you become as happy as Hye Ri, Eun Ho? 

284
00:25:10,950 --> 00:25:12,620
No.

285
00:25:13,780 --> 00:25:17,560
I lived as her for three years,

286
00:25:20,870 --> 00:25:22,600
but not at all.

287
00:25:24,300 --> 00:25:26,570
Actually, Eun Ho...

288
00:25:26,570 --> 00:25:31,310
you came to see me many times as Hye Ri.

289
00:25:31,310 --> 00:25:34,970
But the fact that you don't remember suggests you have

290
00:25:34,970 --> 00:25:39,200
Dissociative Identity Disorder.

291
00:25:45,240 --> 00:25:47,540
Doctor, are you saying...

292
00:25:49,270 --> 00:25:52,780
I'm no longer pretending to be Hye Ri,

293
00:25:53,580 --> 00:25:56,010
but that I've truly become her?

294
00:25:56,010 --> 00:25:59,880
Is that why I wrote that letter to myself when I was Hye Ri?

295
00:26:02,950 --> 00:26:06,020
Could I read the letter?

296
00:26:11,990 --> 00:26:15,730
   

297
00:26:15,730 --> 00:26:18,820
   

298
00:26:18,820 --> 00:26:23,320
 I'm writing because I want to tell you something. 

299
00:26:23,320 --> 00:26:29,080
 I found happiness, and I don't want to let it go. 

300
00:26:29,080 --> 00:26:31,570
 Because... 

301
00:26:31,570 --> 00:26:34,680
   

302
00:26:34,680 --> 00:26:39,900
   

303
00:26:39,900 --> 00:26:43,220
 So I'd like to make a request. 

304
00:26:44,060 --> 00:26:48,380
 Even if you're the owner of this body, 

305
00:26:48,380 --> 00:26:53,250
 please give it to me because I'm happy. 

306
00:26:53,250 --> 00:26:56,660
   

307
00:26:56,660 --> 00:26:58,670
 Because... 

308
00:26:59,630 --> 00:27:04,220
 I'm much happier than you are. 

309
00:27:09,600 --> 00:27:13,800
Look. You can see here

310
00:27:13,800 --> 00:27:17,050
how you were as Hye Ri.

311
00:27:17,050 --> 00:27:20,770
When you first came to me, I recorded you with your consent.

312
00:27:20,770 --> 00:27:22,580
Let me see it, please.

313
00:27:24,390 --> 00:27:26,100
Are you sure?

314
00:27:26,100 --> 00:27:29,000
Yes. I want to see it.

315
00:27:30,160 --> 00:27:34,940
 Then what happens to me, Ju Hye Ri? 

316
00:27:34,940 --> 00:27:37,540
 Do I disappear? 

317
00:27:37,540 --> 00:27:39,780
 Do I go away? 

318
00:27:40,540 --> 00:27:44,890
 Eun Ho has existed only in my dreams. 

319
00:27:44,890 --> 00:27:48,800
 Doctor, I'm happy now. 

320
00:27:48,800 --> 00:27:51,110
 I don't want to abandon Hye Ri. 

321
00:27:51,110 --> 00:27:57,530
 At least, in the present, I am much happier than Eun Ho from my dreams. 

322
00:27:57,530 --> 00:27:59,020
Doctor.

323
00:27:59,020 --> 00:28:01,660
Yes, Eun Ho. Go ahead.

324
00:28:02,460 --> 00:28:05,190
Did Ju Hye Ri seem...

325
00:28:08,550 --> 00:28:10,920
happy to you, too?

326
00:28:27,370 --> 00:28:29,220
What did the doctor say?

327
00:28:32,200 --> 00:28:35,200
What? Is it serious?

328
00:28:37,830 --> 00:28:39,960
No.

329
00:28:39,960 --> 00:28:42,740
Wasn't that Sunbae Shin Joong on the phone?

330
00:28:43,800 --> 00:28:46,140
- Yes. 
 - What did he say?

331
00:28:46,140 --> 00:28:48,100
Today is Department Head Oh's last day.

332
00:28:48,100 --> 00:28:51,260
Really? I thought he was retiring at the end of the year.

333
00:28:51,260 --> 00:28:55,290
Yes, but it must have been decided last month.

334
00:28:56,260 --> 00:28:59,910
So after the holidays, you'll take over the nine o'clock news.

335
00:29:01,530 --> 00:29:02,840
I'm not sure.

336
00:29:02,840 --> 00:29:05,090
What do you mean you're not sure?

337
00:29:05,970 --> 00:29:08,190
I think it's leaking.

338
00:29:09,820 --> 00:29:11,750
This? I found it on the street.

339
00:29:11,750 --> 00:29:13,270
Wait, for real?

340
00:29:13,270 --> 00:29:14,930
Would it be fake?

341
00:29:14,930 --> 00:29:18,020
Why did you have to pick up a broken one?

342
00:29:19,080 --> 00:29:23,190
That's probably why it got thrown out. Then I found it.

343
00:29:23,190 --> 00:29:25,240
It wouldn't have been thrown out otherwise.

344
00:29:25,240 --> 00:29:27,660
That seems logical.

345
00:30:01,100 --> 00:30:05,100
Excuse me. Did Ju Hye Ri not come to work again?

346
00:30:06,670 --> 00:30:09,330
No. She didn't.

347
00:30:09,330 --> 00:30:11,510
She usually does.

348
00:30:13,330 --> 00:30:15,490
Did she not work yesterday either?

349
00:30:16,090 --> 00:30:17,880
No.

350
00:30:17,880 --> 00:30:20,460
You can't reach her, either?

351
00:30:21,780 --> 00:30:23,550
No, I mean...

352
00:30:24,210 --> 00:30:26,650
Ju Hye Ri doesn't have a phone.

353
00:30:28,470 --> 00:30:32,560
I thought so, too, but remember when she passed out in the restroom?

354
00:30:32,560 --> 00:30:35,880
At that time... Hold on a second.

355
00:30:37,490 --> 00:30:40,470
 This was on the floor next to her. 

356
00:30:42,000 --> 00:30:44,100
- It's a phone. 
 - Yes.

357
00:30:44,100 --> 00:30:46,710
But it won't turn on, even after I charged it.

358
00:30:46,710 --> 00:30:48,990
I don't know whose this is.

359
00:30:48,990 --> 00:30:51,490
But I can't ask unless she's here.

360
00:30:51,490 --> 00:30:54,600
Hye Ri doesn't have a phone, and I don't have her address.

361
00:30:54,600 --> 00:30:58,700
Can I take that to her?

362
00:30:59,270 --> 00:31:02,070
I do know her address.

363
00:31:02,070 --> 00:31:03,810
Oh.

364
00:31:06,300 --> 00:31:09,080
Sure. Of course.

365
00:31:14,360 --> 00:31:16,030
Thank you.

366
00:31:19,110 --> 00:31:21,030
 Excuse me! 

367
00:31:24,480 --> 00:31:28,640
If you see Hye Ri, could you tell her something for me?

368
00:31:29,500 --> 00:31:31,330
Tell her what?

369
00:31:31,970 --> 00:31:33,920
That she's dead meat.

370
00:31:36,490 --> 00:31:37,930
Okay.

371
00:32:04,350 --> 00:32:07,130
If you're hungry, should I make you something?

372
00:32:12,620 --> 00:32:16,180
Are you hungry? Want me to make you something?

373
00:32:18,860 --> 00:32:20,710
Yes.

374
00:32:20,710 --> 00:32:22,950
I want something delicious.

375
00:32:22,950 --> 00:32:26,110
Got it. I'll make you something delicious.

376
00:32:27,460 --> 00:32:30,350
Something high in calories.

377
00:32:30,350 --> 00:32:32,120
Not that.

378
00:32:32,120 --> 00:32:34,790
Do you know how puffy your face looks onscreen these days?

379
00:32:34,790 --> 00:32:37,370
Like you eat late every night.

380
00:32:40,330 --> 00:32:42,170
What's this?

381
00:32:46,840 --> 00:32:48,500
It's nothing important.

382
00:32:48,500 --> 00:32:50,260
Are you knitting these days?

383
00:32:50,260 --> 00:32:52,410
You must have a lot of time on your hands.

384
00:32:52,410 --> 00:32:54,130
What? No.

385
00:32:54,130 --> 00:32:56,870
So what will you make me?

386
00:32:58,020 --> 00:33:00,280
Tomato and egg stir fry?

387
00:33:00,280 --> 00:33:03,930
Wow. Sounds good.

388
00:33:27,930 --> 00:33:32,750
   

389
00:33:32,750 --> 00:33:36,990
Special live broadcast of "The Country Right Now and Us" for the Golden Holidays.

390
00:33:36,990 --> 00:33:40,870
Hello, we are at the "Square Meeting" rest stop.

391
00:33:40,870 --> 00:33:46,240
People traveling this weekend can stop and rest a while. 
    

392
00:33:46,240 --> 00:33:49,910
Yes. Rain that started at the beginning of the holiday weekend

393
00:33:49,910 --> 00:33:53,390
has subsided, excluding a few areas in the Seoul region.

394
00:33:53,390 --> 00:33:56,590
Forecasts predict that rain will resume tomorrow morning,

395
00:33:56,590 --> 00:34:01,360
but right now, it's busy here with people enjoying the long weekend.

396
00:34:01,360 --> 00:34:04,670
Should we chat with one of those people?

397
00:34:06,230 --> 00:34:08,450
Please call Yoo Ra.

398
00:34:09,370 --> 00:34:12,500
The main writer, Yoo Ra.

399
00:34:12,500 --> 00:34:14,220
Call her.

400
00:34:14,220 --> 00:34:17,280
She's not picking up my calls.

401
00:34:17,280 --> 00:34:19,570
Oh, well, that's...

402
00:34:19,570 --> 00:34:22,150
Unnie did arrive here...

403
00:34:22,150 --> 00:34:27,160
I mean, she's not here. No, she wasn't able to...

404
00:34:27,160 --> 00:34:28,760
Then...

405
00:34:29,690 --> 00:34:32,170
could you deliver

406
00:34:32,170 --> 00:34:36,500
to Yoo Ra what I have to say?

407
00:34:36,500 --> 00:34:39,370
Yes. If you tell me, I'll deliver the message.

408
00:34:39,370 --> 00:34:41,050
I was...

409
00:34:41,960 --> 00:34:44,770
told I'd be the main emcee.

410
00:34:44,770 --> 00:34:48,290
But I didn't even get the first greeting.

411
00:34:48,290 --> 00:34:54,560
I kept being asked to do people's interviews or to laugh at dumb jokes.

412
00:34:54,560 --> 00:34:56,370
That's...

413
00:34:57,190 --> 00:34:59,710
not how it should be.

414
00:34:59,710 --> 00:35:01,290
And her...

415
00:35:01,290 --> 00:35:03,380
That Baek Hye Yeon.

416
00:35:05,330 --> 00:35:08,120
I've been doing this for 15 years, longer than she has,

417
00:35:08,120 --> 00:35:12,410
but my role is smaller than hers.

418
00:35:12,410 --> 00:35:17,980
What do you think will happen if you keep doing this?

419
00:35:23,920 --> 00:35:26,290
 Do you have a phone? 

420
00:35:26,290 --> 00:35:30,800
 Unfortunately, I get no joy out of the selfishness of civilization. 

421
00:35:46,510 --> 00:35:49,500
Sunbae, I'm scared.

422
00:35:49,500 --> 00:35:52,300
That sunbae…

423
00:35:52,300 --> 00:35:56,510
How should I say this? I think she might kill me.

424
00:35:56,510 --> 00:35:58,800
She wouldn't kill me, would she?

425
00:35:58,800 --> 00:36:04,490
Or, Sunbae, I think that sunbae might beat me up.

426
00:36:04,490 --> 00:36:09,150
Sunbae, I've been bullied a lot, but I've never been beaten.

427
00:36:09,150 --> 00:36:10,850
Will I get beaten?

428
00:36:10,850 --> 00:36:13,830
It would be my first time. I'm scared.

429
00:36:13,830 --> 00:36:16,980
Sunbae, is she always that scary?

430
00:36:16,980 --> 00:36:21,570
You know… my heart is pounding.

431
00:36:23,950 --> 00:36:25,700
But…

432
00:36:27,070 --> 00:36:30,730
how do you contact someone with a broken phone

433
00:36:31,480 --> 00:36:34,130
or no phone at all?

434
00:36:34,130 --> 00:36:36,700
How would I know that?

435
00:36:42,040 --> 00:36:43,920
Hello.

436
00:36:43,920 --> 00:36:48,930
I'm looking for a parking booth employee's contact information.

437
00:36:48,930 --> 00:36:50,450
Yes. Sure.

438
00:36:50,450 --> 00:36:52,820
I'm aware.

439
00:36:54,000 --> 00:36:55,960
Are you crazy?

440
00:36:57,450 --> 00:37:00,530
I'm asking you. Are you crazy?

441
00:37:00,530 --> 00:37:03,210
- Well… 
 - What did you say when you called me a month ago?

442
00:37:03,210 --> 00:37:05,820
"Unnie, we're doing a special holiday live broadcast."

443
00:37:05,820 --> 00:37:09,130
"We will tour rest stops in the country, end up in Busan, and raise money."

444
00:37:09,130 --> 00:37:10,800
"It's a highly well-intended program."

445
00:37:10,800 --> 00:37:15,920
"Unnie, I want you to be the main emcee on this event."

446
00:37:15,920 --> 00:37:17,680
"What do you think, Unnie?"

447
00:37:17,680 --> 00:37:21,840
Does standing in line make me the main emcee?

448
00:37:21,840 --> 00:37:24,100
- It's not like that… 
 - Answer me, Yoo Ra.

449
00:37:24,100 --> 00:37:26,760
Is that what you call a main emcee?

450
00:37:26,760 --> 00:37:28,790
Well, I don't think so.

451
00:37:28,790 --> 00:37:30,650
How do I say this?

452
00:37:30,650 --> 00:37:35,470
Although we are both the lead emcees, Baek Hye Yeon is the host.

453
00:37:35,470 --> 00:37:37,610
But what about me?

454
00:37:37,610 --> 00:37:41,500
I feel like an extra next to her.

455
00:37:44,220 --> 00:37:45,930
 Excuse me. 

456
00:37:47,930 --> 00:37:49,380
- Me? 
 - Yes.

457
00:37:49,380 --> 00:37:51,730
Mi Rae says she won't do it.

458
00:37:52,920 --> 00:37:56,400
- Do what? 
 - She says she won't host anymore.

459
00:37:56,400 --> 00:37:59,490
She is so angry at you that she won't do it,

460
00:37:59,490 --> 00:38:01,950
but as you know, we are totally ruined without her.

461
00:38:01,950 --> 00:38:05,170
She says she's skipping all the rest stop shots from now on.

462
00:38:05,170 --> 00:38:08,330
Well, fine. I can deal with that.

463
00:38:08,330 --> 00:38:13,790
But if she misses filming tomorrow, we're completely doomed.

464
00:38:15,210 --> 00:38:18,030
So I'm asking you.

465
00:38:18,030 --> 00:38:20,770
Please convince Mi Rae.

466
00:38:20,770 --> 00:38:23,000
I begged, but it didn't work.

467
00:38:23,000 --> 00:38:26,600
Please help me out.

468
00:38:29,000 --> 00:38:32,800
This is a special holiday live broadcast of "The Country Right Now and Us."

469
00:38:32,800 --> 00:38:35,350
We are at Mangjoong Rest Stop.

470
00:38:35,350 --> 00:38:39,660
We're much closer to the beaches of Busan.

471
00:38:39,660 --> 00:38:42,780
What's the weather like in Busan right now?

472
00:38:42,780 --> 00:38:46,220
It's very clear in Busan.

473
00:38:46,220 --> 00:38:48,160
Could you introduce yourself first?

474
00:38:48,160 --> 00:38:51,360
Oh, yes. Me? I…

475
00:38:53,290 --> 00:38:55,450
We've met before.

476
00:38:55,450 --> 00:38:57,950
I've seen you before. For sure.

477
00:39:00,000 --> 00:39:01,700
Yes.

478
00:39:01,700 --> 00:39:06,170
 Hello. There's no need to go in person to experience Busan's weather. 

479
00:39:06,170 --> 00:39:09,500
 - Since the age we are living in…  
 - Darn it.

480
00:39:09,500 --> 00:39:13,610
 - has highly developed technology.  
 - Is he on Media N Seoul right now?

481
00:39:13,610 --> 00:39:15,980
 AI is changing our world… 

482
00:39:15,980 --> 00:39:17,250
Did he get permission?

483
00:39:17,250 --> 00:39:20,730
 Even so, we are still living in an analog reality. 

484
00:39:21,950 --> 00:39:25,340
Should I have had my makeup done?

485
00:39:30,190 --> 00:39:31,820
Excuse me.

486
00:39:32,950 --> 00:39:34,310
Me?

487
00:39:34,310 --> 00:39:35,850
Excuse me.

488
00:39:36,720 --> 00:39:38,930
You said you knew me earlier.

489
00:39:39,620 --> 00:39:45,880
Of course, I do. I've seen you talking to Ju Eun Ho's sister.

490
00:39:45,880 --> 00:39:47,500
Well…

491
00:39:48,160 --> 00:39:50,330
who's Ju Eun Ho?

492
00:39:51,480 --> 00:39:55,910
Tomorrow we will gather in the lobby at 10 a.m. and go to the studio together.

493
00:39:55,910 --> 00:39:57,480
 Got it! 
   

494
00:39:57,480 --> 00:40:00,700
 Great work! Thank you! 
   

495
00:40:14,970 --> 00:40:17,200
 Do you live with your family? 

496
00:40:17,200 --> 00:40:19,260
 No, I live alone. 

497
00:40:19,260 --> 00:40:22,420
 I guess you can say I'm an only child. 

498
00:40:38,840 --> 00:40:40,730
Hey.

499
00:40:40,730 --> 00:40:42,440
You know…

500
00:40:45,300 --> 00:40:48,600
I've done the seven, eight, and nine o'clock news.

501
00:40:48,600 --> 00:40:51,410
That means I have as much,

502
00:40:51,410 --> 00:40:55,780
no… more recognition than you.

503
00:40:55,780 --> 00:41:01,100
Do you know what that Press Director scumbag called me and said?

504
00:41:02,730 --> 00:41:06,610
That I should be thankful to be on TV.

505
00:41:06,610 --> 00:41:08,920
Why?

506
00:41:08,920 --> 00:41:11,140
Because I'm old.

507
00:41:12,800 --> 00:41:16,450
But everyone gets old,

508
00:41:16,450 --> 00:41:18,110
including you.

509
00:41:18,990 --> 00:41:23,500
I'm saying… you'll meet a hoobae like you in a few years,

510
00:41:23,500 --> 00:41:27,400
and you'll be fuming, just like me.

511
00:41:34,290 --> 00:41:36,400
I'm sorry,

512
00:41:36,400 --> 00:41:41,200
but I have no intention of sharing a room with you.

513
00:41:42,770 --> 00:41:44,860
Excuse me, Sunbaenim.

514
00:41:46,550 --> 00:41:48,890
Why? What?

515
00:41:51,300 --> 00:41:56,320
I won't share a room with you. I won't complain.

516
00:41:58,730 --> 00:42:02,140
Could you please do the broadcast tomorrow?

517
00:42:02,140 --> 00:42:07,030
I'll ask the Press Director if we can split the lines.

518
00:42:09,870 --> 00:42:12,580
I beg you, Sunbaenim.

519
00:43:01,900 --> 00:43:04,410
Hey, it's me.

520
00:43:04,410 --> 00:43:06,380
Where are you?

521
00:43:07,760 --> 00:43:09,830
Can you maybe…

522
00:43:11,030 --> 00:43:13,630
come here right now?

523
00:43:36,140 --> 00:43:38,540
Do you have trouble waking?

524
00:43:38,540 --> 00:43:41,440
How can you sleep for 12 hours at a time?

525
00:43:41,440 --> 00:43:45,270
Maybe you have a sleep disorder, not a panic disorder.

526
00:43:47,030 --> 00:43:50,190
Is it morning or not?

527
00:43:50,190 --> 00:43:53,200
"Morning"? It's evening.

528
00:43:56,080 --> 00:43:57,580
Well, I…

529
00:43:57,580 --> 00:43:59,810
What? What?

530
00:44:01,530 --> 00:44:04,600
Did I wake up at some point?

531
00:44:04,600 --> 00:44:07,780
- Did I… 
 - What are you saying?

532
00:44:07,780 --> 00:44:11,950
I thought you were dead. I kept checking to see if you were breathing.

533
00:44:14,340 --> 00:44:17,640
Where did you find those clothes?

534
00:44:18,330 --> 00:44:22,020
